GameOver - Class in com.mygdx.game.screens
The Game Over screen displays the same background image as the Main Menu and allows the user to try again with the same class, choose a different class, or exit the game.
GameOver(Malice, Music, Player, String) - Constructor for class com.mygdx.game.screens.GameOver
Creates a GameOver screen and stores the Malice object that created this screen, the music currently playing, the player object from Game Screen, and the class that the player chose.
GameScreen - Class in com.mygdx.game.screens
GameScreen handles gameplay and manages the interaction between the map, characters, and projectiles.
GameScreen(Malice, Music, String) - Constructor for class com.mygdx.game.screens.GameScreen
Creates a CharacterSelect screen and stores the Malice object that created this screen, the music currently playing, and the class that the player chose.
GameScreen.State - Enum in com.mygdx.game.screens
Enum for handling the various states of the game screen.
generate(int) - Method in class com.mygdx.game.world.Map
Generates the map based on type of generation This method should be used instead of randomGeneration() as it will take in consideration all types of generations (this method is mainly for expansion of game generation)

getDirection(float, float) - Method in class com.mygdx.game.player.Enemy
Returns the Direction that the given parameters indicate If both deltaX and deltaY are greater than the marginOfDelta, move diagonal else if one of them is greater than the marginOfDelta, move straight in that direction else return -1 after above conditions are met, EAST when deltaX is positive and WEST when negative NORTH when deltaY is positive and SOUTH when negative
